## **What This Visual Mapper Does:**

### **Features:**

1. âœ… **Shows slide preview** - Renders the first slide as an image
1. âœ… **Highlights text boxes** - Color-coded (Blue=unmapped, Green=mapped, Yellow=selected)
1. âœ… **Click to select** - Click any text box to select it
1. âœ… **Assign to field** - Map selected text box to current field
1. âœ… **Visual feedback** - See all mappings in real-time
1. âœ… **Legend** - Shows what each color means
1. âœ… **Field labels** - Mapped fields show their name on the preview
1. âœ… **Mapping list** - See all current mappings at a glance
1. âœ… **Progress tracking** - Shows how many fields are mapped (X of 7)

### **User Workflow:**

1. Click **â€œVisual Field Mapperâ€** button
1. Select a PowerPoint file
1. **Visual mapper opens** showing slide with highlighted text boxes
1. Select field from dropdown (WI_Number, Revision, etc.)
1. **Click on the text box** containing that fieldâ€™s value
1. Click **â€œAssign to Fieldâ€**
1. Repeat for all fields
1. Click **â€œSave Mappingsâ€**

### **Color Legend:**

- ğŸŸ¦ **Blue** = Unmapped text box
- ğŸŸ© **Green** = Mapped text box (shows field name label)
- ğŸŸ¨ **Yellow** = Currently selected text box

